Hollande Has Most Support as Presidential Candidate, Poll Shows

-- B y   A l b e r t i n a   T o r s o l i
-- 
2011-08-21T17:41:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/hollande-has-most-support-as-presidential-candidate-poll-shows.html
The French public backs  Francois Hollande , a contender for the Socialist Partyâ€™s 2012
presidential nomination, as the next president of France, a poll
for the newspaper  Liberation  showed today.  Forty seven percent of respondents supported Hollande while
29 percent of those polled wanted President  Nicolas Sarkozy  to
be re-elected, the survey showed.  The poll was conducted by Viavoice for Liberation. Viavoice
questioned 1,003 people aged 18 and older by telephone on Aug.
18 and Aug. 19. For questions with at least 1,000 respondents,
the poll had a margin of error of 1.8 percentage points to 3.1
percentage points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
